  "body": "### The Issue\r\nWhen sending ether to a non-payable function, Brownie currently returns a generic \"reverted\" message without a useful code highlight. This can be very confusing / challenging to debug.\r\n\r\n### Proposed Fix\r\nDuring compilation, locate the bytecode that handles reverts this situation, and attach a custom error string to the `REVERT` using similar functionality to existing developer revert strings.\r\n\r\nThe series of opcodes should be something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nJUMPDEST, CALLVALUE, DUP1, ISZERO, PUSH1, JUMPI, PUSH1, DUP1, REVERT\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks to @manfr3d for suggesting this improvement (#255)",
